$ desk.cpl

*Desktop Settings → Windows/control-panel[Control Panel]*, for example to change the screen resolution or → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/desk_cpl/primary-secondary-monitor_resolution-etc#primary-monitory[primary/secondary monitor].

This dialog can also be opened on the command line with
code {
→ Windows/settings#setting-command-line[start] ms-settings:display
code }

More traditionally, this dialog is also opened by with a mouse right click on the desktop and then choosing *Display Settings*.

gh|Windows-Pics|/cpl/desk/top-portion.png||

{ Multiple displays #desk_cpl-multiple-displays

  Apparently, the options that are found in the listbox below *Multiple displays* can somewho be triggered from the command line with
  → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/DisplaySwitch_exe[`DisplaySwitch.exe`].

}

sa:
  Some settings seem to be stored in the → Windows/registry under
  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/System/CurrentControlSet/Control/GraphicsDrivers/Configuration/_id_[`HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\System\CurrentControlSet\Control\GraphicsDrivers\Configuration\_id_`].
